1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,067
<i> Ahh!</i>

2
00:00:02,667 --> 00:00:03,700
<i>- Ahh!
- Sari!</i>

3
00:00:05,900 --> 00:00:07,133
Is this what you're looking for?

4
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:11,200
<i>- Oro Viejo.
- It's a map.</i>

5
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:13,533
<i>They say it's just part
of a bigger map.</i>

6
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:16,700
<i>And now that you've seen this,
your lives are in danger.</i>

7
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:18,133
<i> You have to be careful.</i>

8
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:21,200
<i> Leon!</i>

9
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:25,267
<i>Dela Paz is talking to someone
in the city jail to shut you up.</i>

10
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:28,067
<i>I don't think you had anything
to do with Juan's murder.</i>

11
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,633
<i>- Hello? Sir?
- Why are you messing</i>

12
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:30,667
<i> with my things?!</i>

13
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,267
[GUNSHOT]

14
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:41,633
<i>- Jade called. Leon escaped.
- What?</i>

15
00:00:46,733 --> 00:00:48,967
- I need to go.
- [TRIXIE] Wait, Justin!

16
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:51,633
Let him go.
They need him right now.

17
00:00:51,767 --> 00:00:53,067
He has to go home.

18
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,867
[MARTIN] What do you mean
Leon escaped?

19
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,533
Have they found him yet?

20
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:58,467
Jade doesn't know anything yet.

21
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,567
But when they were going
to the provincial jail,

22
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:03,133
that's when Leon fought
and escaped.

23
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:04,800
[MARTIN] Why did he do that?

24
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:07,233
We're already looking
for a way to free him! Leon!

25
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,433
- My god, Leon!
- [TRIXIE] Martin, listen.

26
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,800
Let's just look for him, okay?

27
00:01:10,933 --> 00:01:14,133
Because once the cops find him,
especially that Marina,

28
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:15,467
we don't know what she could
do to Leon.

29
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:18,000
- Okay? Let's just look for him.
- [CHESKA] Social media groups

30
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:19,400
might help us.

31
00:01:19,533 --> 00:01:22,933
Let's check Kaluguran's page.
T-That's always up-to-date.

32
00:01:23,067 --> 00:01:24,800
Something might have happened,
someone must have seen it.

33
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:26,033
Let's check it now.

34
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:28,233
[MARTIN] Kiko,
talk to the boatmen.

35
00:01:28,367 --> 00:01:31,067
Ask them if they saw anything,
or if they know anything.

36
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,467
But don't ever tell them
it might be Leon.

37
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:36,133
- Okay? Leon needs to be safe.
- Okay.

38
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:37,833
[MARTIN BREATHING HEAVILY]

39
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,733
[GROANING]

40
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:48,233
[BREATHING RAPIDLY]

41
00:01:48,367 --> 00:01:51,667
[PHONE BUZZING]

42
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:53,433
- [CHESKA] Check the recent--
- Hello?

43
00:01:54,167 --> 00:01:55,067
[LEON] Martin.

44
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,333
[LEON BREATHING HEAVILY]

45
00:01:56,467 --> 00:01:58,800
<i> It's me. Don't say a word.</i>

46
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,467
<i>Just listen
to what I have to say.</i>

47
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:05,833
I need your help.

48
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:08,267
Please.

49
00:02:08,967 --> 00:02:09,967
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

50
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,233
You have to come to me.

51
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:14,400
Don't tell the others.

52
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:16,233
Okay.

53
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:18,833
[TRIXIE] Martin,
where are you going?

54
00:02:18,967 --> 00:02:21,833
[MARTIN] Justin!
I'm going to Kaluguran, too!

55
00:02:21,967 --> 00:02:23,267
[JUSTIN] Why?

56
00:02:24,267 --> 00:02:25,433
[MARTIN] There's somewhere
I need to go.

57
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:27,100
[JUSTIN] Come on.

58
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:34,300
[BOAT ENGINE REVVING]

59
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:39,233
[GROANING]

60
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:45,900
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

61
00:02:47,867 --> 00:02:54,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:48,933
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]
- [LEON BREATHING HEAVILY]

63
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:51,033
[MARTIN] Leon?

64
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:52,367
Leon!

65
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:53,467
Leon!

66
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,733
- [WEAKLY] Martin...
- Leon--

67
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:55,933
- Martin!
- Leon!

68
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:58,967
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:03:59,100 --> 00:03:59,967
[MARTIN WHISPERS] Leon...

70
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:01,067
Bro...

71
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:02,433
My god.

72
00:04:04,433 --> 00:04:06,233
Come on, let's get you up.

73
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:08,800
[LEON GROANING IN PAIN]

74
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:10,933
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

75
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:17,433
Leon, this is going to hurt.

76
00:04:17,567 --> 00:04:18,500
This is going to hurt.

77
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:21,600
- [LIQUID POURING]
- [SCREAMING IN PAIN]

78
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:23,900
[GRUNTING]

79
00:04:24,033 --> 00:04:25,167
Let's wrap your wound.

80
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,667
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

81
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,500
Let go.

82
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:28,867
Remove your hand, Leon.

83
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:34,033
[LEON BREATHING SHARPLY]

84
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:35,100
[MARTIN] Inhale.

85
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:36,100
[LEON INHALES DEEPLY]

86
00:04:36,967 --> 00:04:37,933
[MARTIN] Exhale.

87
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:40,467
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

88
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,800
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

89
00:04:43,933 --> 00:04:45,000
[BREATHING STEADILY]

90
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:48,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

91
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:49,733
What were you thinking?

92
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,833
Why did you run away?

93
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,900
Sir Henri...

94
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,767
He helped me.

95
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,433
He let you escape?

96
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:05,033
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

97
00:05:05,167 --> 00:05:07,433
He himself helped me escape.

98
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:08,667
How?

99
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:12,300
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:05:12,433 --> 00:05:15,433
They have plans against me
in my new prison.

101
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:18,267
[LEON] Martin,

102
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:21,867
Sir Henri believes
that I am innocent.

103
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,467
[MARTIN] That means
he believed us when we said

104
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:27,000
that De La Paz had something
to do with everything.

105
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:29,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

106
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:30,433
Kiko said...

107
00:05:30,567 --> 00:05:32,700
you're all looking
for the treasure.

108
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:35,233
Leon, stop this.

109
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,533
Look at yourself.

110
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:38,033
Forget about the treasure.

111
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:43,733
We will uncover the truth
once we find it.

112
00:05:43,867 --> 00:05:47,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

113
00:05:47,167 --> 00:05:49,900
Now, tell me, Martin.

114
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,933
What did you see?

115
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,567
What did you find?

116
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:59,900
We arrived at the shrine
on the mountain, Leon.

117
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:03,467
We saw something up there.

118
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:11,500
[MARTIN] A map.

119
00:06:18,367 --> 00:06:20,533
At least you're
on the right track.

120
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,600
Edward?

121
00:06:26,267 --> 00:06:27,467
Edward!

122
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:29,867
- Edward, my siblings are here.
- Jade...

123
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,533
If they see you--

124
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:33,600
- Edward, please leave.
- Jade, Jade.

125
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,133
I'm sorry.

126
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:37,600
What?

127
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:39,500
Why?

128
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,833
- Edward, why are you--
- I'm really sorry, Jade.

129
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,133
For everything.

130
00:06:45,533 --> 00:06:46,500
Huh?

131
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,667
What are you saying?

132
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,733
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

133
00:06:51,867 --> 00:06:52,867
Jade.

134
00:06:53,967 --> 00:06:55,367
Of all people,

135
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:58,267
you're the one
I don't want to see hurt.

136
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:03,033
I would never hurt you.

137
00:07:04,367 --> 00:07:05,867
- Okay?
- Edward...

138
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:09,033
- Remember that. Okay?
- What's the problem?

139
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:11,567
[JADE] Did you have
a fight with Uncle Andy?

140
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,567
What? Did he say anything?

141
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,400
Did something happen
back home?

142
00:07:15,567 --> 00:07:17,667
Edward, what is it?
I'll listen.

143
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:21,633
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

144
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:23,133
Edward, please.

145
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:25,033
Say something.

146
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:26,900
What's going on with you?

147
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,200
I'm sorry, Jade.

148
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,167
[JADE] Why?

149
00:07:33,967 --> 00:07:36,167
Edward, I don't understand.

150
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:39,333
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:40,667
Edward.

152
00:07:41,433 --> 00:07:42,667
Edward!

153
00:07:46,167 --> 00:07:47,233
Edward!

154
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:48,967
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

155
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:49,867
[JADE] Edward...

156
00:07:53,133 --> 00:07:54,833
[ENGINE STARTS]

157
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,267
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

158
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,767
Leon! Leon, come on!

159
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:00,633
- No, go on without me.
- Please! Leon, come on!

160
00:08:00,767 --> 00:08:01,767
- Leon, let's go!
- Just leave--

161
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,133
- Please!
- Martin, leave me here!

162
00:08:03,267 --> 00:08:04,067
Please, Leon! Come with me!

163
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,733
- Leave me here, Martin!
- Let's go!

164
00:08:06,567 --> 00:08:07,767
Please!

165
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:13,800
I don't want them to worry.

166
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,833
So, please! Leave me here.

167
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:23,967
- [SIREN WAILING CONTINUES]
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

168
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:26,433
- Martin.
- Let's go, Leon...

169
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:29,033
- Come on.
- You take care of them.

170
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:32,267
Of Mom.

171
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:35,800
Of Luna.

172
00:08:38,133 --> 00:08:39,267
Of Justin.

173
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Of Jade.

174
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,467
Just go, Martin.

175
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,600
Please.

176
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:50,367
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

177
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:52,000
Leave me.

178
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:53,600
Go!

179
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:56,200
[SIREN WAILING CONTINUES]

180
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:57,333
Here.

181
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:01,467
You'll find
many rides downtown,

182
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,400
so head that way.

183
00:09:03,533 --> 00:09:04,567
Please.

184
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,233
You're safe there.

185
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:08,033
[LEON] Go, Martin!

186
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:09,800
Go!

187
00:09:09,933 --> 00:09:16,100
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

188
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:20,067
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

189
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,767
[WHIMPERS, SNIFFLES]

190
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:25,667
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

191
00:09:26,867 --> 00:09:28,200
Just tell us, Mrs. Almazan!

192
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,833
Where did your son go?

193
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:31,467
I already told you.
I have no idea.

194
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,667
[MARINA] You have no idea?

195
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,300
Or do you just
not want to say it?

196
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,300
Did you know that you can
be an accessory to

197
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:38,333
the crime if you don't tell us
what you know?

198
00:09:38,467 --> 00:09:40,567
I already said, I don't know!

199
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:42,933
You've been searching here
for a while now!

200
00:09:43,067 --> 00:09:44,933
But did you find anything?

201
00:09:45,067 --> 00:09:48,133
Did you see anyone talk
to me on the phone?

202
00:09:48,267 --> 00:09:50,800
What you mean is that you've
planned this for a long time.

203
00:09:51,533 --> 00:09:52,967
So that's why you were so calm,

204
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,467
when you informed
each other earlier.

205
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,867
[SCOFFS]

206
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,833
What are you even talking about?

207
00:09:57,967 --> 00:09:59,967
[KIKO] Ma'am, the way
you're interrogating her

208
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,200
doesn't sound nice anymore.

209
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:04,033
Auntie Frida has already
answered you.

210
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:05,300
She doesn't know anything.

211
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:07,467
If you don't believe that,
well, that's your problem.

212
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,667
[JADE] Kiko.

213
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:11,467
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,867
[LUNA] Mom!

215
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,900
[KIKO] If you still don't
believe her...

216
00:10:18,233 --> 00:10:21,467
then go out and look for Leon.

217
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:24,633
You won't find
any information here.

218
00:10:24,767 --> 00:10:26,367
We don't know anything.

219
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:28,700
We're just asking questions,
Miss Luna.

220
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,267
[LUNA] And I'll answer again.

221
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,300
Just talk to our lawyers.

222
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:34,767
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

223
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:36,200
[KIKO] Martin.

224
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:39,333
Where have you been?

225
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:40,600
Uh...

226
00:10:40,733 --> 00:10:43,633
I just went to
Leon's golf buddies.

227
00:10:44,067 --> 00:10:46,033
[MARTIN] He might've
come to them.

228
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:49,567
See?
You found nothing, didn't you?

229
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:57,033
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:05,100
[LEON BREATHING HEAVILY]

231
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:15,267
[GULPING]

232
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:18,967
[PANTING]

233
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:26,100
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:27,833
Kiko.

235
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:32,567
[MARTIN] Give me a heads-up
if they're already coming back.

236
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:34,200
All right.

237
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,133
Auntie.

238
00:11:41,767 --> 00:11:43,433
- Yes?
- I met with your son.

239
00:11:43,567 --> 00:11:44,800
What?

240
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:47,533
[MARTIN] I met with Leon
before coming here.

241
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:49,967
Where is he?

242
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:52,133
Is he okay?

243
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:56,133
He's...
He's fine.

244
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:57,333
Fine?

245
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:03,100
Mom, don't speak loudly.
They might hear you.

246
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:06,967
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

247
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:08,767
[INHALES SHARPLY] Please.

248
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:11,133
I need to talk to him.

249
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:16,467
[FRIDA BREATHING HEAVILY]

250
00:12:16,633 --> 00:12:17,900
Call.

251
00:12:19,067 --> 00:12:24,167
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

252
00:12:24,633 --> 00:12:25,867
[CELLPHONE BEEPING]

253
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,367
Unreachable.

254
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:30,500
[FRIDA] Martin,
why did you leave him?

255
00:12:30,633 --> 00:12:32,000
Where is he?

256
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:34,533
I asked him
to come home, Auntie.

257
00:12:34,667 --> 00:12:36,133
But he didn't want to.

258
00:12:36,567 --> 00:12:37,633
But why?

259
00:12:37,767 --> 00:12:44,900
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:49,867
- Why?
- De La Paz...

261
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:51,900
The police officer.

262
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,267
She's planning to do
something bad to him.

263
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:57,200
That's why Sir Henri was
forced to let him escape.

264
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:59,700
Oh my God.

265
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:01,900
My son, Leon!

266
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:04,300
[FRIDA] No.

267
00:13:04,433 --> 00:13:05,467
If that's the case,

268
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,967
then why are they still
not arresting De La Paz?

269
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,667
I don't know.

270
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:11,667
Maybe the evidence they have
isn't strong enough yet.

271
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,400
They might still be looking
for more concrete proof.

272
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:16,933
[MARTIN EXHALES]
What's clear to me now is...

273
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:19,900
that he doesn't want
you all to get involved in this.

274
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:21,300
[FRIDA EXHALES DEEPLY]

275
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:23,833
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:27,733
I need to see him, Martin.
I need to see Leon.

277
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:29,367
Where is he?

278
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:31,833
Auntie, I can't.

279
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:32,967
[FRIDA SIGHS]

280
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,367
I'm sorry.

281
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,167
My Leon...

282
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:47,133
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

283
00:13:47,267 --> 00:13:52,333
[GROANING IN PAIN]

284
00:13:54,100 --> 00:14:00,333
[PANTING SLOWLY]

285
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:04,800
[LEON GRUNTING]

286
00:14:04,933 --> 00:14:11,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:17,367
[GRASS RUSTLING]

288
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,733
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

289
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:32,567
[BODY THUDS]

290
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,700
<i>- Surprise!
- Surprise!</i>

291
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:40,700
<i>- Happy birthday!
- Happy birthday!</i>

292
00:14:41,467 --> 00:14:44,667
<i>Wow! It's our first time to
get out like this in a while.</i>

293
00:14:45,367 --> 00:14:48,033
[FRIDA]<i> And we should
</i> do this more often.

294
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:49,867
[BLOWS]

295
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,767
<i> - Wow!
</i>- Yehey! What did you wish for?

296
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:54,433
<i>- Happy birthday, brother!
- Happy birthday!</i>

297
00:14:54,567 --> 00:14:56,400
<i> Happy birthday, Justin!</i>

298
00:14:57,133 --> 00:14:58,433
[FEDERICO]<i> If you let your
</i>emotions get the better of you,

299
00:14:58,567 --> 00:15:01,367
<i>it will affect your mother
as well as your siblings.</i>

300
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:03,767
<i> We're doing this for them.</i>

301
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:06,600
<i> I hope your dad can see this.</i>

302
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,133
<i>I'm sure that he can
see us, Mom.</i>

303
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:12,800
[MOTIVATIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:15,700
[LEON]<i> Leon, you need
</i> to do this.

305
00:15:18,067 --> 00:15:20,067
<i>You still have
to return to them.</i>

306
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:26,700
[FRIDA]<i> Your dad won't
</i>forgive me if I lose one of you.

307
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:28,533
[FEDERICO]<i> Your Uncle Mike
</i> and I are fixing everything.

308
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:31,067
[FRIDA]<i> I won't be able
</i> to forgive myself either.

309
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:32,900
[FEDERICO] This never happened.

310
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:34,100
[LEON] Dad.

311
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,200
[FEDERICO]<i> Promise me.
</i> This never happened!

312
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:36,933
[LEON] I saw him, Dad.

313
00:15:37,067 --> 00:15:39,100
[FEDERICO] Shh! Listen to me.

314
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:42,300
<i>You didn't kill him, okay?
You didn't kill anyone!</i>

315
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,100
[SCREAMS]

316
00:15:45,567 --> 00:15:50,400
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,167
[SCREAMS] Aah!

318
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:53,133
[THUDS]

319
00:15:53,133 --> 00:15:55,333
- [GRUNTS]
- [LEON CHOKING] You're alive...

320
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:59,067
Yes, your dads
failed to kill me!

321
00:15:59,433 --> 00:16:01,400
That's why you killed my son!

322
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:04,333
- [SANDRO GRUNTING]
- [LEON CHOKING]

323
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:06,133
I didn't kill Juan!

324
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,267
[LEON GROANS] Agh!

325
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:11,167
[LABORED BREATHING STOPS]

326
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:16,600
[SANDRO BREATHING HEAVILY]

327
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:29,033
[GRASS RUSTLING]

328
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:45,367
[WAVES CRASHING]

329
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:52,400
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

330
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:06,467
- [CAR BEEPS]
- [MARTIN] Sir.

331
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:09,200
Can I talk to you?

332
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:11,200
Is that urgent, Martin?

333
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,800
I have to be
at the police station.

334
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,267
I need to update the Chief.

335
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,333
[MARTIN EXHALES]

336
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:20,033
I heard that you helped
my friend escape.

337
00:17:21,467 --> 00:17:22,567
Did you guys meet?

338
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,467
Where is he?

339
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,067
Is it true?

340
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:28,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

341
00:17:28,267 --> 00:17:29,467
Does that mean...

342
00:17:29,467 --> 00:17:32,133
you believe that Dela Paz
has something to do with this?

343
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:35,100
I don't know
what you're talking about.

344
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:39,067
Leon wouldn't lie.

345
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:42,333
And he wouldn't have
the guts to escape

346
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:44,133
if it weren't for your help.

347
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:48,333
I'm sorry.
But you're wrong, Martin.

348
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:52,367
Now, if you won't tell me
where Leon is,

349
00:17:52,367 --> 00:17:54,167
there's nothing more
we can talk about.

350
00:17:58,433 --> 00:17:59,600
I didn't see him.

351
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:03,267
And I don't know where he is.

352
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:07,700
[HENRI] Alright. I'm leaving.

353
00:18:09,867 --> 00:18:11,333
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

354
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,467
[CAR DOOR CLOSES, ENGINE STARTS]

355
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:19,567
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

356
00:18:19,567 --> 00:18:24,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

357
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:26,233
How are we going to know
if Leon is safe?

358
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:29,200
Martin said he is.
Let's just trust him.

359
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:31,800
He's safer
wherever it is he is hiding.

360
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:33,867
Mom said she's going
to talk to the attorney

361
00:18:33,867 --> 00:18:36,300
to find someone
who'll look for Leon.

362
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:37,867
We can't just wait here
and do nothing.

363
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,833
[JUSTIN]
And we can't trust the police.

364
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:44,133
I still believe that Dela Paz
and Andy are conspirators.

365
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:46,167
But it's true that Andy
is interested in the treasure.

366
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:47,500
Why?

367
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:49,200
What happened, Luna?

368
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,333
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:52,700
His men attacked us
while we were looking for clues.

370
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:54,267
- What? Are you okay?
- [JADE] What?

371
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,267
- Luna, are you okay?
- Did you get hurt?

372
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,300
[LUNA] I'm fine.

373
00:18:56,300 --> 00:18:59,667
It helped that
we expected that to happen.

374
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:05,600
That means he believed the clues
that we offered before.

375
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,400
He may not admit it,

376
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:07,767
but he's getting
closer and closer

377
00:19:07,767 --> 00:19:09,300
to the trap we had planned.

378
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:11,700
[JADE]
Gio and the others were right.

379
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:15,267
This treasure
will answer a lot of things.

380
00:19:15,733 --> 00:19:17,267
Not just for Leon's sake...

381
00:19:18,433 --> 00:19:20,300
but also for Dad and Uncle Mike.

382
00:19:23,733 --> 00:19:24,867
We got this.

383
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:31,567
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

384
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:36,567
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]
- [FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

385
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:51,267
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

386
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:53,633
[BODY THUDS]

387
00:20:02,533 --> 00:20:06,467
- [WATER TRICKLING]
- [HEAVY FOOTSTEPS]

388
00:20:21,467 --> 00:20:28,400
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

389
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:47,800
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

390
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:51,867
Why can't we go see him?
We'll be careful.

391
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:52,833
That's not enough reason.

392
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,467
The cops aren't just
monitoring the Almazans.

393
00:20:55,667 --> 00:20:56,800
They're keeping an eye
on us, too.

394
00:20:56,933 --> 00:20:58,933
What if they follow us
and catch Leon?

395
00:20:59,467 --> 00:21:01,500
But Jade wants to see
her brother.

396
00:21:02,167 --> 00:21:03,500
She needs to be patient.

397
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:05,500
This is for the safety
of all of us.

398
00:21:05,633 --> 00:21:08,767
Can you call him?
Just to make sure he's okay.

399
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:14,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:21:15,033 --> 00:21:17,133
[LINE RINGING]

401
00:21:17,267 --> 00:21:18,200
It's ringing.

402
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:22,300
[LINE RINGING CONTINUES]

403
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:27,500
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

404
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:32,733
[RINGING STOPS]

405
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:43,900
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

406
00:21:44,067 --> 00:21:47,900
[METAL CHAIN RATTLES]

407
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:51,700
[LINE RINGING]

408
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:52,867
He's not answering.

409
00:21:53,533 --> 00:21:55,033
But at least
it's ringing, right?

410
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:57,900
That means he's still there.
He hasn't given up.

411
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:08,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

412
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:29,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

413
00:22:32,467 --> 00:22:34,500
<i> Jade told Edward...</i>

414
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:36,600
that we are suspicious of Andy,

415
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:38,567
<i> and also about the treasure.</i>

416
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:39,933
[SLAMS]

417
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,000
<i> Jade, that's so stupid!</i>

418
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:46,233
<i>I'm not asking you for money.
I'm borrowing.</i>

419
00:22:46,367 --> 00:22:47,533
<i>How are you going
to pay me back?</i>

420
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:52,333
<i> I didn't kill Juan.</i>

421
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:54,833
<i>It's Uncle Andy
and his accomplice who's a cop.</i>

422
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,233
<i> They killed Juan!</i>

423
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:58,167
<i> Andy Arellano killed Juan!</i>

424
00:22:58,300 --> 00:22:59,233
[STEEL CLANKS]

425
00:22:59,367 --> 00:23:00,467
<i> You're too loud!</i>

426
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,133
<i> Try to talk again...</i>
